<h3 id="fibula-type">Fibula Type</h3>
<p>Crossbow</p>
<h3 id="description">Description</h3>
<p>This is a heavy Crossbow fibula with three onion-shaped knobs and a short flat catch plate. It has intricate design patterns all along the brooch of flower-like patterns. Along the foot it has a similar patter to the bow and small knobs along the edge. There is also a ribbed pattern on the crossbar of the fibula. It has a large bow that is short in length but has a high arch.</p>
<h3 id="culture">Culture</h3>
<p>Roman</p>
<h3 id="period">Period</h3>
<p>Byzantine</p>
<h3 id="date">Date</h3>
<p>Second half of 4th century CE</p>
<h3 id="material">Material</h3>
<p>Gilt copper alloy with niello inlay</p>
<h3 id="size">Size</h3>
<p>L: 8.8 cm, W: 6.2 cm, D: 3.2 cm</p>

<h4 id="accession-number">Accession Number</h4>
<p><a href="https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/470294">1999.42</a></p>

